snippet: Eel populations, which had been declining on the East Coast, are making a comeback on Staten Island, with large numbers of them appearing earlier than normal.
abstract: Eel populations are making a comeback in creeks of Staten Island, with large numbers appearing a month earlier than normal; popular as bait and food and crucial to the food chain, eels have been declining in East Coast rivers and the influx is deemed a testament to cleaner conditions.
lead_paragraph: Eel populations, which had been declining on the East Coast, are making a comeback on Staten Island, with large numbers of them appearing earlier than normal.

headline.seo: Eels Visit Staten Island Early and in Great Numbers
headline.main: Back on Staten Island Early, and Wriggling
